Introduction

VANNER is a five-member boy group under KLAP Entertainment. The group consists of Yeonggwang, Gon, Taehwan, Hyesung, and Sungkook. They made their official debut in Korea on February 14, 2019, with the studio album "V" but they have already been promoting in Japan since 2018.

The group's name is a combination of the words "Victory" and "Banner" which is significant to their aim of putting a flag of victory on top.

On January 21, 2023, it was confirmed that VANNER will compete in JTBC's Peak Time. On the last episode aired on April 19, VANNER was revealed to be the winner of the show.

On May 4, KLAP Entertainment announced that they signed a three-year contract with VANNER.
